# 🚀 CSE First Year Roadmap  
### Beginner → Future Software Engineer

Welcome.

If you're in **Computer Science Engineering – First Year**  
and your goal is to become a **Software Engineer**,  
this roadmap is built for you.

This is not hype.  
This is execution.

---

# 🧠 PHASE 1: Build Strong Foundations (0–6 Months)

## 1️⃣ Learn One Programming Language Properly

Choose ONE:

- C++
- Java
- Python

Do not jump languages.

Focus on:
- Variables
- Data Types
- Loops
- Functions
- Arrays
- Strings
- Basic OOP

🎯 Goal:
Be able to solve basic logic problems confidently.

---

## 2️⃣ Start Problem Solving

Platform suggestions:
- LeetCode
- CodeStudio
- CodeChef

Start with:
- Basic loops
- Pattern problems
- Arrays
- Strings

🕒 Target:
3–5 problems per week minimum.

Consistency > Intensity.

---

## 3️⃣ Understand How Computers Actually Work

Learn:
- What is RAM?
- What is CPU?
- What is Stack vs Heap?
- How compilation works
- What is Git?

You’re a CSE student.
You must understand systems.

---

# 🧱 PHASE 2: Core Engineering Growth (6–12 Months)

Now things get serious.

## 4️⃣ Data Structures & Algorithms (DSA)

Learn:
- Arrays
- Strings
- Linked List
- Stack
- Queue
- Recursion
- Sorting
- Binary Search
- Basic Trees

Not just theory.
Solve problems.

🎯 Target:
150–200 questions by end of First Year.

---

## 5️⃣ Learn Git & GitHub

You must know:

- git clone
- git add
- git commit
- git push
- branches

Build public repositories.

Your GitHub = Your Resume.

---

## 6️⃣ Build Small Projects

Examples:

- Calculator (CLI or Web)
- To-Do App
- Basic Portfolio Website
- Simple Login System
- Quiz App

Rule:
Every 2–3 months → Build something.

---

# 🌐 PHASE 3: Choose Direction (End of First Year)

Now explore:

## Option A: Web Development

Learn:
- HTML
- CSS
- JavaScript
- React (later)

Build:
- Landing Pages
- Dashboards
- Blog UI
- Small SaaS Clone

---

## Option B: Backend Development

Learn:
- Node.js or Java Spring
- APIs
- Databases (MongoDB / MySQL)

Build:
- REST API
- Auth system
- CRUD apps

---

## Option C: Competitive Programming

If you love logic:

- Practice daily
- Learn STL
- Learn Time Complexity deeply

---

# 🏗️ DAILY STRUCTURE (Simple System)

If you have 1 hour daily:

30 min → DSA  
20 min → Development  
10 min → Revision  

If you have 2–3 hours:

1 hr → DSA  
1 hr → Project  
30 min → Concepts  

---

# 🧩 SKILL STACK YOU MUST BUILD

✔ Problem Solving  
✔ Git  
✔ Basic Web  
✔ OOP  
✔ Debugging  
✔ Reading Documentation  

---

# 📊 FIRST YEAR TARGET CHECKLIST

- [ ] 200 DSA problems
- [ ] 3–5 Projects
- [ ] Active GitHub
- [ ] One domain clarity
- [ ] Resume draft ready

---

# ⚠️ COMMON MISTAKES TO AVOID

❌ Watching tutorials without coding  
❌ Learning 5 languages at once  
❌ Ignoring DSA  
❌ Not building projects  
❌ Comparing yourself daily  

---

